24d48/src/integrators/integrator_utils.jl#L195-L204

`integrator.t` is snapped to the `tstop` if it's close enough. However, after this `t` adjustment then https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/da5d57ca7a59757768a1206f272f88ae72624d48/src/integrators/integrator_utils.jl#L206 is called and if there is a continuous callback then https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/da5d57ca7a59757768a1206f272f88ae72624d48/src/integrators/integrator_utils.jl#L259 is called. this leads to a short visit in DiffEqBase, https://github.com/SciML/DiffEqBase.jl/blob/93190126e5aa39d4ab5fcaebd8b310b30b4d91f7/src/callbacks.jl#L496. The `time` variable passed to `apply_callback!` looks like it's computed with root finding and this can cause ` != integrator.t` in https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/da5d57ca7a59757768a1206f272f88ae72624d48/src/integrators/integrator_interface.jl#L10-L16 which will overwrite `integrator.t`.

In my example, `t` after the last step is `479.83333333333337` and the `tstop` is `479.8333333333333` so `integrator.t` is snapped to `tstop`. But after the call to `apply_callback!`, `integrator.t` has been reverted to the original value. I should mentioned that the time values here are inside two layers of `ForwardDiff.Dual`s. Unfortunately, I haven't been able to reduce this error to a self contained example.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1600/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1600/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null}}

